  <h2>Food Pairing Guide</h2>

<p>Merlot's supple tannins and fruit-forward character create exceptional flavor bridges with a diverse range of cuisines. The wine's moderate acidity and plush texture complement both rich proteins and earthy vegetables, while its characteristic plum and chocolate notes enhance dishes with similar flavor profiles.</p>

<h3>Classic Pairings That Work</h3>

<ul class="space-y-2">
<li><strong>Herb-Crusted Lamb:</strong> Merlot's soft tannins won't overpower delicate lamb, while the wine's herbal undertones mirror rosemary and thyme seasonings perfectly.</li>

<li><strong>Duck Confit with Cherry Sauce:</strong> The wine's natural cherry and plum flavors create a seamless bridge with fruit-based sauces, while the richness matches the duck's fat content.</li>

<li><strong>Mushroom Risotto:</strong> Earthy Merlots from cooler climates complement umami-rich mushrooms, with the wine's creamy mouthfeel matching the risotto's texture.</li>

<li><strong>Dark Chocolate Desserts:</strong> Right Bank Bordeaux Merlots often display chocolate notes that harmonize beautifully with cocoa-based desserts, creating flavor amplification rather than competition.</li>

<li><strong>Grilled Portobello Burgers:</strong> The meaty texture of portobellos matches Merlot's substantial body, while the wine's fruit character balances the mushroom's earthiness.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Regional Traditions</h3>

<p>In Bordeaux's Right Bank, Merlot traditionally pairs with <strong>côte de boeuf</strong> and aged cheeses like Roquefort. Tuscan Merlots shine alongside <strong>wild boar ragu</strong> and pecorino, while Washington State producers recommend their Merlots with <strong>cedar-plank salmon</strong>, showcasing the wine's affinity for both red meat and rich fish.</p>

<h3>Versatile Everyday Options</h3>

<p>For casual dining, Merlot excels with <strong>pizza margherita</strong>, where the wine's acidity cuts through cheese while complementing tomato sauce. <strong>Barbecue ribs</strong> work beautifully, as Merlot's fruit-forward nature balances smoky, sweet glazes without being overwhelmed by bold flavors.</p>

<h3>Special Occasion Selections</h3>

<p>For elegant entertaining, pair aged Pomerol with <strong>beef tenderloin</strong> finished with truffle butter, or serve Napa Valley Merlot alongside <strong>rack of venison</strong> with juniper berries. These combinations showcase Merlot's ability to enhance sophisticated cuisine while maintaining its approachable character.</p>

